Additional history was provided that this patient had a previous diagnosis of endometrial adenocarcinoma.
A. Representative sections through the right hemicolon mass at the ileocecal valve show fragments of colonic wall showing extensive involvement by a moderately differentiated colonic adenocarcinoma.
Within the pericolonic soft tissues, 18 lymph nodes were identified, two of which show evidence of metastatic adenocarcinoma.
Around the periphery of the fragments, some columnar-type atypical epithelium is present similar to that seen within the right colon cancer (specimen A).
The findings are consistent with metastatic colonic adenocarcinoma.
